defaultExample 1b: ‘benchmark’ and variable amountsdefaultA, B and C award themselves ’salaries’ of £20,000, £40,000 and £40,000 respectiv
defaultely and agree that the total profit will be shared in proportion to those salaries.
default If the overall profits of the partnership are more or less than £100,000 then each partner will share in the deficit or surplus in proportion to their agreed salary.  
defaultThis
default arrangement is in substance identical to example 1a: each partner has an interest in the profits of the partnership which is variable by reference to the overall profits of the partnership.  It is not relevant that the partnership has chosen to describe t
defaulthis arrangement by reference to a salary.
defaultExample 1c: guaranteed amountsdefaultContinuing example 1b, individual D joins the LLP.  He is also awarded a ‘salary’.  His total profit share will be calculated as a proportion of the total profits of ABC LLP in the sa
